"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is trying to plot date values on the x-axis, but Matplotlib's plot function doesn't automatically handle dates. It requires the use of date2num to convert the dates to a format that Matplotlib can understand. Also, the plt.text function requires the x-coordinate to be a number, not a datetime object.\",\n  \"patch\": \"15c15\\n< ax.plot(df['C'], df['E'])\\n---\\n> import matplotlib.dates as mdates\\n> ax.plot(mdates.date2num(df['C']), df['E'])\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))\\n17c17\\n< plt.text(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\"), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n> plt.text(mdates.date2num(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\")), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\"\n}"